comments: Thank you for this survey. It has helped me to start thinking about economic differences in the world. Also taking into consideration factors that contribute to this inequality.
Excellent questions - clear and concise layout

I believe the cause of income inequality between nations is by poor economic choices by the government (not because rich countries "exploit" poor ones). The wrong set of policies was implemented, generally Statist policies.
South Africa is a developing country, with the right government who prioritize its citizens, it would be a richest country too since we own many natural resources.
All good. The survey was clear and the questions were straight forward

This was very interesting and particularly the question about the distribution of wealth and the causes. Sometimes I do feel the wealthy countries are to blame as they impose unreasonable barriers on poor countries. But then poor countries are most rife in corruption that exacerbates the poverty issue.
The biggest problem is the west, with being greedy and using its powers to  exploit the rest of the world.
Good questions. Make you think about the state of the nation you live and work in.
a Few solid points were raised. Don't blame your circumstances.
was nice being part of this survey. enjoyed it . it made me question a lot of things
Very interesting set of questions and I'm glad I got to participate.

Nice study but I believe it all differs from which context is this study coming from because it is still the same system that provide low quality education and still expect people to come out of it successful. And the very same education system doesn't fit all people since we are all different. Yes putting in the work can get a person somewhere but it could always mean you are in the wrong space to share your skills because of how everything is set up.
Thanks for the survey it was great.
I like the questions, very interesting.
The questions are very interesting and simultaneously informative.
great surveys, i learned a lot about economic equality and wealth distribution, it is really great when someone asks your opinion. i would like to receive more surveys. i enjoiyed it

Being poor and rich is not 100% dependant on the distribution of resources but I would say is 50% based on GOD or a spirit behind (any), 45% in the mindset and 5% distribution of resources. I always say to people, if you think R1 Million is a lot of money, trust me, you are probably not mentally positioned for real wealth. If you set a ceiling of something in your mindset, that is how far you can go in handling that very same thing.

I personally know a bunch of people who should go on the Moja Love show: I blew it because R500k - R1 million or RAF drove them insane. Distribution of resources was definitely there, but the mental capacity of handling such small money was never there.

There is currently a Character of a young girl on Skeem Saam called Eunice, this girl got R1,7 Million, to say the least such people annoy the GOD out of me. I don't like stupid people like that!
